b|Redcar]] (1)\n*[[Sunderland RFC|Sunderland]] (1)\n*[[Team Northumbria RFC|Team Northumbria]] (1)\n*[[Wallsend RFC|Wallsend]] (1)\n*[[Winlaton Vulcans RFC|Winlaton]] (1)\n*[[Whitley Bay Rockcliff RFC|Whitley Bay Rockcliff]] (1)\n[[Whitby RUFC|Whitby]] (1)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=a}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Durham County Rugby Football Union|Durham RFU]]\n* [[Northumberland Rugby Football Union|Northumberland RFU]]\n* [[English rugby union system]]\n* [[Rugby union in England]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n{{Rugby union in England}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Durham Northumberland 2}}\n[[Category:Rugby union leagues in England|8]]\n[[Category:Rugby union in Northumberland]]\n[[Category:Rugby union in County Durham]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox rugby league football competition\n| name = Durham/Northumberland 2\n| current_season =  2019\u201320 Durham/Northumberland 2\n| logo = England Rugby text logo.svg\n| pixels = \n| sport = [[Rugby union]]\n| founded = {{Start date and age|1987}}\n| teams = 14\n| country = {{ENG}}\n| champion = [[Whitley Bay Rockcliff RFC|Whitley Bay Rockcliff]] (1st title)\n| season = 2019\u201320)<br> (promoted to [[Durham/Northumberland 1]]\n| most_champs = [[Ponteland RFC|Ponteland]] & [[Consett RFC|Consett]]\n| count = 3\n| TV = \n| website    = [http://www.englandrugby.com/fixtures-and-results/competitions/northern-division/2016-2017/group/21288 England RFU]\n}}\n\n'''Durham/Northumberland 2''' is an English Rugby Union league at the eighth tier of the domestic competition for teams from [[North East England]]. The champions and runner-up and promoted to [[Durham/Northumberland 1]] and the bottom two clubs are relegated to [[Durham/Northumberland 3]].  Each season two teams from Durham/Northumberland 2 are picked to take part in the [[RFU Senior Vase]] (a national competition for clubs at level 8) - one affiliated with the [[Durham County Rugby Football Union|Durham County RFU]], the other with the [[Northumberland Rugby Football Union|Northumberland RFU]].  Ponteland won the title in 2020.\n\n==Participating Clubs 2019-20==\n\n{{col-begin|width=100%}}\n\n{{col-break|width=70%}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=100%\n|-\n!|Team\n!|Ground\n!|Capacity\n!|City/Area\n!|Previous season\n|-\n| Ashington || The Recreation Ground || || [[Ashington]], [[Northumberland]] || 6th\n|-\n| Bishop Auckland || West Mills Playing Fields || || [[Bishop Auckland]], [[County Durham]] || 8th\n|-\n| Blyth || Plessey Road || || [[Blyth, Northumberland]] || Promoted from [[Durham/Northumberland 3]] (runners up)\n|-\n| [[Darlington RFC|Darlington]] || Blackwell Meadows || 3,000 || [[Darlington]], [[County Durham]] || 11th\n|-\n| [[Gosforth Rugby Football Club|Gosforth]] || [[Broadway West Sports Ground|Broadway West]] || || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]], [[Tyne and Wear]] || 7th\n|-\n| Hartlepool || Mayfield Park || || [[Hartlepool]], [[County Durham]] || 3rd\n|- \n| Ponteland || Ponteland Leisure Centre || || [[Ponteland]], [[Tyne and Wear]] || Relegated from [[Durham/Northumberland 1]] (13th)\n|-\n| [[Redcar Rugby Union Football Club|Redcar]] || Mackinlay Park || || [[Redcar]], [[North Yorkshire]] || 12th\n|-\n| Ryton || Main Road || || [[Ryton, Tyne and Wear|Ryton]], [[Tyne and Wear]] || 9th\n|-\n| Seaton Carew || Hornby Park || || [[Seaton Carew]], [[County Durham]] || Promoted from [[Durham/Northumberland 3]] (champions)\n|-\n| Sedgefield || Sedgefield Cricket Club || || [[Sedgefield]], [[County Durham]] || 10th\n|-\n| Sunderland || Ashbrooke Sports Club || || [[Ashbrooke]], [[Sunderland, Tyne and Wear|Sunderland]], [[Tyne and Wear]] || 4th\n|-\n| Whitby || Recreation Ground || || [[Whitby]], [[North Yorkshire]] || Relegated from [[Durham/Northumberland 1]] (14th)\n|-\n| Winlaton Vulcans || Axwell View || || [[Winlaton]], [[Blaydon-on-Tyne]], [[Tyne and Wear]] || 5th\n|-\n|}\n\n{{col-break|width=15%}}\n\n{{Location map+|North East E